                            <comment id="14124408" author="rakeshr" created="Sat, 6 Sep 2014 09:49:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about making this as ZooKeeperCriticalThread. I&apos;m planning to handle the exceptions of critical threads by having a special listener. This will make the server down. Please see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1907&quot; title=&quot;Improve Thread handling&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-1907&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-1907&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14487961" author="rakeshr" created="Thu, 9 Apr 2015 18:51:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch, where it does &lt;tt&gt;Leader.LearnerCnxAcceptor&lt;/tt&gt; thread critical. Now, on exception it will notify the listener and by default this will make the server shutdown. Please review. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
